# AI Memory Contract

This file is the tool-neutral session-start contract for AI assistants working
inside HermesAgent. HermesAgent is the renamed/restored HermesNous knowledge
graph. Claude, Codex, Cursor, or other agents should treat this as the shared
memory entry point.

## Critical Memory - 2026-05-24

- User chose migration option 1: rename/rebase HermesNous into HermesAgent.
- Source of truth is the restored `~/ObsidianVault/HermesAgent` graph from `HermesNous.retired-20260524`.
- Multi-AI context and prompt shortcut routing are complete and verified. Start at [[ai-context/README|AI Context Hub]] and [[ai-context/prompt-shortcut-registry|Prompt Shortcut Registry]].
- VPS WebEngine routing as of 2026-06-22: active work moved from the old `synerry_engine`/`synerry-engine` context to `newwebengine2026`. On `linux-nat`, the canonical repo is `/home/linux-nat/SynerryTools/newwebengine2026`, staff worktrees are `/home/linux-nat/.worktree/newwebengine2026/<staff-id>`, and `/srv/projects/synerry-engine` must not be used as the default work target for current WebEngine work. See [[ai-context/worktree-routing-gate|Worktree Routing Gate]].
- Verification gate: `python3 /Users/rattanasak/ObsidianVault/HermesAgent/automation/ai_context_health.py` must return `ok=True` before claiming this setup is 100%.
- The generated standalone `~/ObsidianVault/HermesAgent` created earlier was wrong-scope and is backup/staging only.
- Do not rebuild a separate Knowledge Center from scratch.
- Do not create many new folders/files when an existing layer file can be merged.
- Before creating a new note, scan [[MOC]], [[00-Center/docs/OBSIDIAN_LINK_INDEX]], [[00-Center/docs/AI_SKILL_ROUTER]], [[00-Center/docs/SKILL_GRAPH]], [[95-Inbox-Lab/sources/README]], [[10-Knowledge/README]], [[10-Knowledge/lessons/README]], [[10-Knowledge/patterns/README]], [[50-Playbooks/README]], [[95-Inbox-Lab/review/queue]], and [[skills/README]].
- For news/URL/raw posts, preserve source lineage and place unreviewed material in `sources/` or `review-queue/`; promote only after review.
- For URL/article/social-post knowledge intake, "analyze" means analyze in chat first. Do not write files, create KITS entries, update registries, or promote knowledge until the owner reviews the recommendation and explicitly chooses a route. See [[memory/profile/knowledge-intake-review-before-write|Knowledge Intake Requires Owner Review Before Write]].
- For URL/article/social-post/release-note knowledge intake, "analyze" must include truth check, strengths, weaknesses, project fit, development potential, and Hermes placement decision before routing or writing. See [[memory/profile/knowledge-intake-decision-analysis-required|Knowledge Intake Requires Decision Analysis]].
- When the owner is present and sends a link/post for review, do the decision-grade review immediately in chat. Do not use "review queue" as a way to defer the review; queues are only for post-review follow-up such as sandbox tests, source notes, promotion, issues, or installation, and must include a clear trigger/next action.
- If intake material is installable or upgradeable software (plugin, tool, app, library, release), classify the action explicitly as sandbox install/test, update/upgrade audit, security audit, project issue/plan, or no action. Do not treat software as only a source note.
- Do not create new vaults, projects, repos, or test workspaces for software/plugin testing unless the owner explicitly asks. Use the owner-approved existing target, and define rollback/uninstall steps before or during installation.
- Any installed or upgraded plugin/tool/software trial must have a verification checklist and scheduled evaluation at the owner-defined cadence (for example weekly or one month): pros, cons, risks, continue as real use, continue trial, or uninstall/rollback.
- User language first: answer in the language the owner uses. If the owner writes Thai, answer in Thai and translate unavoidable technical terms into plain business Thai immediately. Do not summarize with English system words only. See [[memory/profile/user-language-first|ใช้ภาษาผู้ใช้ก่อนเสมอ]].
- For MD Assist by AI Asana questions, use only the owner-approved Summary Workload portfolio `1206630289713031` (`https://app.asana.com/0/portfolio/1206630289713031/workload`) plus Dashboard `1206619840648978` (`https://app.asana.com/0/dashboard/1206619840648978`), only users/projects visible through that workload scope, and only data since `2026-01-01` unless the owner explicitly asks for older data. Nat Personal Board live chat should route through live Asana analysis (`#asana`, `#dashboard`, workload/dashboard keywords), not memory alone. Do not scan the whole Asana workspace or old projects. See [[memory/workflow/asana-active-workload-source-of-truth|Asana Active Workload Source Of Truth]].
- Skills and Agents must connect through [[00-Center/docs/AI_SKILL_ROUTER]] and [[00-Center/docs/SKILL_GRAPH]], not through a disconnected new graph.

