## Memory Layers

| Layer | Folder/File | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| active context | `.hermes/active.md` | current work, blockers, next steps |
| working context | `.hermes/context.md` | durable project context for this repo |
| decisions | `.hermes/decisions.md` | decision log with context, chosen path, rejected path |
| atomic memory | `memory/` | compact facts AI should reuse across sessions |
| raw source | `sources/` | curated raw inputs or source pointers |
| promoted knowledge | `knowledge/`, `lessons/`, `patterns/`, `playbooks/`, `training-packs/` | reviewed reusable knowledge |
| active pilot context | `knowledge/owner-context-v0.1.md`, `knowledge/ai-writing-standards-v0.1.md` | owner-approved Phase 1 AI behavior rules |

## Write Rules

- Do not write permanent knowledge directly from a single chat unless the evidence is clear.
- Put uncertain or unreviewed material in [[95-Inbox-Lab/review/queue|review queue]] or `sources/` first.
- Promote only stable, reusable items into `knowledge/`, `patterns/`, `playbooks/`, or `training-packs/`.
- Add atomic facts to `memory/` only when they are short, durable, and useful for future sessions.
- Important architecture or workflow choices must also be logged in `.hermes/decisions.md`.
- For HermesAgent knowledge intake, update existing notes when merge confidence is high; otherwise use `review-queue/` and link back to the source.
- Owner review comes before any KITS/link-intake write unless the owner explicitly says to store, save, add to KITS, promote, or deploy.

## Atomic Memory Criteria

A memory fact should be:

- one durable idea, preference, boundary, or constraint
- backed by a source, decision, lesson, or user instruction
- short enough for an AI to scan quickly
- linked to related knowledge when possible

## Compaction Flow

1. Raw article, session, report, or incident enters `sources/` or [[95-Inbox-Lab/review/queue|review queue]].
2. AI or owner extracts a [[10-Knowledge/lessons/README|lesson]] when there is a clear learning.
3. Repeated lessons become [[10-Knowledge/patterns/README|patterns]].
4. Actionable patterns become [[50-Playbooks/README|playbooks]].
5. Stable reusable instructions update [[10-Knowledge/training-packs/README|training-packs]] or [[00-Center/docs/SKILL_CENTER|Skill Center]].
6. Durable context needed at session start becomes an atomic memory note in `memory/`.
