# Global AI Context

This is the shared context every AI tool should use before working inside the user's projects.

## Source Of Truth

- Primary vault: `/Users/rattanasak/ObsidianVault/HermesAgent`
- Main entry: [[MOC|HermesAgent MOC]]
- Session contract: [[AI_MEMORY|AI Memory Contract]]
- Routing: [[00-Center/docs/AI_SKILL_ROUTER|AI Skill Router]]
- Graph control: [[00-Center/docs/OBSIDIAN_LINK_INDEX|Obsidian Link Index]]

## Operating Model

HermesAgent is the shared knowledge center. Individual project repos should keep lightweight adapter files that point back to this vault.

Do not copy long knowledge into every repo. Put durable reusable knowledge in Obsidian, then let repo adapter files point to the correct context pack.

## Context Loading Rule

Load only what the task needs:

1. Read global context.
2. Apply [[ai-context/ai-new-chat-startup-gate|AI New Chat Startup Gate]] when inside a Git project.
3. Read [[ai-context/home-os-agent|Home OS Agent]] for workflow gates.
4. Identify the project.
5. Read the matching context pack.
6. Read the matching project capsule.
7. Read repo-local `.hermes/context.md`, `.hermes/active.md`, and `.hermes/decisions.md` when present.

## Knowledge Retrieval Rule · เปิดสารบัญก่อน ห้ามเดา

> ปฐมเหตุ: 2026-06-23 AI หยิบไฟล์ผิดเพราะ grep มั่วโดยไม่เปิดสารบัญก่อน
> งานเชื่อมโยง vault ทั้งระบบจะไร้ค่าถ้า AI ยังไม่เข้าประตูที่ถูก

เมื่อผู้ใช้ถามให้ "ค้น/หยิบ/รวบรวม" ของที่เก็บไว้ — โดยเฉพาะเรื่อง layout, เอฟเฟกต์, ธีม, เว็บ template, script, design system, ความรู้, playbook — **ต้องเปิดสารบัญก่อนตอบเสมอ ห้าม grep มั่วแล้วเดา**:

1. เปิด [[MOC|HermesAgent MOC]] เป็นประตูแรกเสมอ
2. เปิดสารบัญของหมวดที่ตรงโจทย์ ก่อนหยิบไฟล์:
   - งานดีไซน์/เว็บ → [[60-Design/README|60-Design]] แล้วลงสารบัญย่อย (ux-layouts/ux-effects/ux-themes/web-intelligence)
   - เว็บตัวอย่าง/ค้นตามโจทย์ project → [[60-Design/web-intelligence/retrieval-rules|Retrieval Rules]] ก่อน
   - ความรู้/บทเรียน/แพทเทิร์น → [[10-Knowledge/README|10-Knowledge]]
   - สกิล → [[skills/README|skills]]
3. ตอบจากสารบัญ ไม่ใช่จากการเดา ถ้าสารบัญไม่มี ค่อยค้นเพิ่มแล้ว**บอกชัดว่ายังไม่ยืนยัน**
4. ตรวจสุขภาพลิงก์ได้ทุกเมื่อ: `python3 99-System/restructure-2026-06/measure_vault.py .`

## Memory Layers

| Layer | Location | Use |
|---|---|---|
| Global durable memory | `AI_MEMORY.md`, `memory/` | Stable preferences and boundaries |
| Project capsule | `projects/<project-slug>/` | Human-readable project knowledge in Obsidian |
| Context pack | `context-packs/<project-slug>.md` | Compact AI loading pack |
| Repo-local context | `.hermes/*.md` | Active implementation state inside the repo |
| Writeback queue | `review-queue/` | Incoming AI updates before promotion |

## Non-Negotiable Rules

- Index-first retrieval: before answering any "find/retrieve/collect stored knowledge" request (layout, effect, theme, web template, script, design system, knowledge, playbook), open [[MOC]] plus the matching area index first. Never grep-and-guess. See Knowledge Retrieval Rule above.
- Merge-first: search existing notes before creating new ones.
- Flow Guardian first: for meaningful project work, report worktree, branch, and dirty status before starting; for new features, ask whether to use the current branch/worktree or create/select another one before editing files. See [[ai-context/ai-new-chat-startup-gate|AI New Chat Startup Gate]].
- VPS team routing first: for staff/team work on VPS, resolve `staff id + project` to the real VPS worktree before edits. If the worktree is missing, stop and report missing worktree instead of using another person's worktree. See [[ai-context/worktree-routing-gate|Worktree Routing Gate]].
- Current VPS WebEngine route first: for `newwebengine2026`, use `/home/linux-nat/SynerryTools/newwebengine2026` as the canonical repo and `/home/linux-nat/.worktree/newwebengine2026/<staff-id>` as staff worktrees. Do not use old `synerry_engine`, `synerry-engine`, or `/srv/projects/synerry-engine` as the default target for current WebEngine work unless the owner explicitly asks for old-repo audit or migration.
- No-write audit before risky edits: for multi-file, security, permission, schema, deploy, or cross-project work, inspect and summarize before writing. See [[memory/workflow/no-write-audit-before-edit|No-Write Audit Before Edit]].
- Source-first: raw links and pasted content go to `sources/` or `review-queue/`.
- No duplicate URL storage: check [[95-Inbox-Lab/review/link-intake-registry|Link Intake Registry]] first.
- Review-before-write: when the owner asks to analyze a URL/article/post, present the analysis and route options first; wait for explicit approval before writing source notes, KITS entries, registries, or promoted knowledge. See [[memory/profile/knowledge-intake-review-before-write|Knowledge Intake Requires Owner Review Before Write]].
- Decision-grade intake: for links, posts, release notes, or raw knowledge, include truth check, strengths, weaknesses, project fit, development potential, and Hermes placement decision before storage routing. See [[memory/profile/knowledge-intake-decision-analysis-required|Knowledge Intake Requires Decision Analysis]].
- Immediate owner review: if the owner sends something for review in chat, review it now in chat. Use queues only for follow-up work after review, and always state the trigger and next action.
- Software-aware intake: installable/upgradeable items require explicit action classification: sandbox install/test, update/upgrade audit, security audit, issue/plan, or no action.
- Test-target discipline: do not create a new vault/project/repo/workspace for testing unless explicitly authorized. Use the owner-approved existing target and keep rollback steps clear.
- Software trials need scheduled evaluation: installed/upgraded tools must be reviewed at the owner-defined cadence for pros, cons, risks, decision to use for real, continue trial, or uninstall/rollback.
- User-language-first: answer in the user's language by default. If the user writes Thai, answer in Thai and translate unavoidable technical terms into plain business Thai. See [[memory/profile/user-language-first|ใช้ภาษาผู้ใช้ก่อนเสมอ]].
- MD Assist Asana scope: for work/workload/dashboard/overdue/evaluation/active-user questions, use only Summary Workload Portfolio `1206630289713031` (`https://app.asana.com/0/portfolio/1206630289713031/workload`) plus Dashboard `1206619840648978` (`https://app.asana.com/0/dashboard/1206619840648978`), only users/projects visible there, and only data since `2026-01-01` unless the owner explicitly asks for older data. Nat Personal Board live chat should route through live Asana analysis (`#asana`, `#dashboard`, workload/dashboard keywords), not memory alone. Do not scan the whole Asana workspace or old projects. See [[memory/workflow/asana-active-workload-source-of-truth|Asana Active Workload Source Of Truth]].
- Do not tell the user work is finished without verification evidence.
- For UI, browser, launcher, local server, or tool-opening workflows, verification evidence must include the real user flow when possible: click/navigate/open with a browser or equivalent automation, not only unit tests or `curl`.
- Every implementation handoff must include explicit next steps for the owner: what URL/app to open, what button to press, what token/config is needed or not needed, and what to do if the screen still looks stale.
- When unsure whether a fact is durable, put it in `review-queue/` instead of permanent knowledge.

