# Prompt Shortcut Registry

This is the shared prompt shortcut contract for Codex, Qwen, Claude Code, Gemini, Cursor, and future AI tools.

## Runtime Rule

When the user invokes a shortcut, the AI must read the mapped prompt file and apply it to the current task. Do not paraphrase, invent, or partially apply the shortcut.

## Shortcut Map

| Shortcut | Aliases | Prompt File | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| `Use Act-As` | `use-act-as`, `Use Act As`, `Act-As`, `act-as`, `ใช้ Act-As`, `กำหนดบทบาท`, `เรียกทีมผู้เชี่ยวชาญ` | [[skills/prompt-shortcuts/references/use-act-as|use-act-as]] | v3.0 (Memory Schema v1.1, lifecycle step 1) · Read memory + prior decisions before planning, define expert roles, split work, and build a 2–5 phase plan with shared phase ids (P1, P2…) whose verify points cite the Evidence Ladder (§4) and branch/worktree; on approval writes `.hermes/plan.md` for Comply/Continue. No file changes until approved. |
| `Use Comply` | `use-comply`, `Comply`, `comply`, `ใช้ Comply`, `ทำ Comply`, `แตกเฟส`, `ทำตารางเปอร์เซ็นต์` | [[skills/prompt-shortcuts/references/use-comply|use-comply]] | v3.0 (Memory Schema v1.1, lifecycle step 2) · Read `.hermes/plan.md` then break each phase into detailed issues under the same ids (P1-I1…), auto-detect the repo's quality gate, and score numeric compliance where verified=100% only; the iron rule "no pasted output = claimed" plus §11 status mapping keep % honest and feed Close cleanly. |
