## Tool-Specific Loading

| Tool | Native route | Required behavior |
|---|---|---|
| Codex | `$prompt-shortcuts` skill via `/Users/rattanasak/.codex/skills/prompt-shortcuts` | Load the skill and then the mapped reference prompt. |
| Claude Code | `CLAUDE.md` project/global memory | Read this registry, then open the mapped prompt file from Obsidian. |
| Gemini CLI | `GEMINI.md` project/global memory | Read this registry, then open the mapped prompt file from Obsidian. |
| Qwen | `QWEN.md` or `AGENTS.md` project memory | Read this registry, then open the mapped prompt file from Obsidian. |
| Cursor | `.cursor/rules/obsidian-context.mdc` | Read this registry, then open the mapped prompt file from Obsidian. |

## Verification Standard

The setup is considered ready only when:

1. Codex skill symlink points to `skills/prompt-shortcuts`.
2. Every repo adapter file references this registry.
3. Adapter templates include this registry for future projects.
4. The health check fails if any required adapter cannot see prompt shortcuts.

## Project-Wide Status

As of 2026-05-28, the project-wide owner rules rollout points every real Viber Project AI instruction file to this registry. Agents must treat Thai aliases and English aliases as equivalent shortcut invocations.

As of 2026-05-28, the original four mapped prompt files are upgraded to detailed v2 prompts. As of 2026-05-29, `Use Summary` is added for link-plus-content intake review before durable writes. As of 2026-05-30, `Use Scan Feature` is added for evidence-first repo feature extraction. As of 2026-05-31, `Use Business Plan` is added for reusable business, marketing, pitch, tender, website, and strategy question review, and `Use WOW Resource` is added for WOW System plus Web Design Intelligence resource selection without direct script copying. As of 2026-06-01, `Use Viber Structure` is added for Viber Code / Vibe Code Enterprise project structure, artifact, tracker, and quality-gate generation, `Use Viber Audit` is added for evidence-based Viber Enterprise Standard checks across one or many projects, and `Use Impeccable` is added as the single owner-facing shortcut for Impeccable UI slop detection, installation, scanning, fixing, and review workflow. As of 2026-06-06, `Use Flow Guardian` is added for Home OS Agent startup discipline, worktree/branch safety, no-write audit, approval gates, verification, tracking, and handoff, and `Use New Chat` is added to force real startup checks before any “ready for commands” response. As of 2026-06-07, `Use Blog Auto` is added for Hi Logic Labs blog orchestration, privacy gate, Obsidian index, Content Factory handoff, and draft-first owner approval. As of 2026-06-07, `Go to Sleep` is renamed to `Use Continue`; the old sleep wording remains only as a legacy alias so AI tools continue work instead of interpreting the shortcut as a stop/sleep instruction. As of 2026-06-07, `Use Save Git` is added as the owner-facing safe Git/GitLab/VPS shipping gate before push, merge, deploy, and final SHA/health claims. As of 2026-06-08, `Use Save Git` v1.3 removes copyable bad examples and pairs the prompt with runtime gate output that returns `REMEDIATE_DIRTY_WORKTREE_NOW` plus required AI follow-up instead of stop-at-audit wording. As of 2026-06-08 (later same day), `Use Save Git` is rebuilt as v2 after reviewing 11 real project failures of merge/push-to-production loops: v1.3 is retired and the old action-based flow must not be used. v2 makes the gate a single runnable 5-stage check (`save_git_gate.py --stage merge-gate|ship-gate`) driven by a per-project `.savegit.json` adapter, verified to block on secret files, scope-bloat/wrong-target MRs, and failed/old-commit health endpoints, returning one decision token plus a Grid that names the real blocking layer. Redesign evidence: `95-Inbox-Lab/review/save-git-redesign/evidence-and-review.md`. As of 2026-06-22, `Use Move Folder` is added to route Hermes and other AI tools to the existing VPS cleanup/move workflow under `/home/linux-nat/.codex/use-move-folder/project-registry` instead of falsely treating the shortcut as missing. As of 2026-06-25, `Use Move Folder` is upgraded to v1.1 after a two-AI review (Claude draft plus GPT-5.5 Codex cross-check): adds an `Operational Safety Gate` (live `NO_TOUCH_POLICY.md` first, `realpath` source/dest, no-touch plus `DEC-039` duplicate-canonical-folder check, filesystem-boundary `rsync --dry-run`, exact command plus rollback/verify plan, exact-scope approval), three end-of-phase decision tokens (`MOVE_SAFE_BATCH_PROPOSED`, `MOVE_OWNER_DECISION_REQUIRED`, `MOVE_BLOCKED_NO_TOUCH`), a no-fabricate rule when the VPS is unreadable, and marks the in-file protected-roots list as a non-authoritative snapshot. The mapped prompt files remain the source of truth.

As of 2026-06-09, `Use AI Relay` is added as a proven, token-saving variant of `Use AI Pair`: Claude only plans, picks the coder, reviews, and decides, while a cheaper non-Claude coder writes the code (Grok as default via headless terminal, Codex for hard backend via cross-check `ask_gpt5`, Gemini for large UI). It loops fix->review until 100% before the phase gate opens, and carries a per-project setup checklist (owner must add `Bash(grok:*)`/`Bash(gemini:*)` via `/permissions` since AI cannot self-grant) plus connection-reality notes. Proof case: master-webengine 2026-06-09 — Grok headless file write and Claude review verified end-to-end.

As of 2026-06-25, three shortcuts that already had complete, in-use prompt files but were missing from the Shortcut Map table are registered so registry and source-of-truth folder match (18 → 21): `Use AI Pair` (multi-AI Planner/Coder/Reviewer flow), `Use Business Plan` (v2.0 business/marketing/pitch/tender/website/strategy reviewer with Module Router), and `Use SaaS Opus Master Prompt` (full SaaS master planner prompt). Note: `Use SaaS Opus Master Prompt` overlaps heavily with `Use Business Plan` (persona/journey/pricing/pitch/WOW) — kept for now because the owner asked it to be remembered and resent verbatim, but it is a future merge candidate.

As of 2026-06-26, six shortcuts are unified into one connected system governed by a single shared contract, `Memory Schema v1.1` (`skills/prompt-shortcuts/references/memory-schema.md`) — the one source of truth for memory file shapes, the verified-vs-claimed rule, the Evidence Ladder, quality-gate auto-detection, shared phase/issue ids, status mapping, the autonomy policy, and the ledger. The five lifecycle prompts are replaced in place to match: New v1.7, Close v2.0, Act-As v3.0, Comply v3.0, Continue v4.0. A plain-language owner guide (`memory-system-owner-guide-th.md`) explains the system for non-dev owners. Version lock (checked on start): Schema v1.1 ↔ Close ≥ v2.0 ↔ New ≥ v1.7 ↔ Act-As ≥ v3.0 ↔ Comply ≥ v3.0 ↔ Continue ≥ v4.0.

Lifecycle — each step reads the previous step's output via the `.hermes/` files and reuses the same ids, so work hands off without loss:

```
New (open + read memory/token)
  → Act-As (plan into phases + ids → write .hermes/plan.md on approval)
    → Comply (break issues under the same ids + % + evidence)
      → Continue (execute phase by phase + ledger)
        → Close (verify, write memory, emit decision token)
```

Design invariants that make every shortcut work on the VPS, on every project, and on each staff laptop: capability-based gates (check only what the repo has), no hardcoded paths/IPs (read from project config; `$ROOT` differs local vs VPS), per-staff routing, and a version lock between paired prompts. Two safety notes: merge→main / production deploy / prod migration are OUT of auto by default (`ALLOW_AUTO_PROD=OFF`); and the deploy-verify step lists both GitHub (`gh`) and GitLab (`glab`) commands because real project CI runs on GitLab.

As of 2026-06-26, `Use Create Design System` v1.0 is added (21 → 22). It is not built from scratch: it stitches three existing assets plus one new gate. The front (Phase 0, business-brief-to-design-direction) reuses the global design-system library and the `design-selector` skill; the back (Phase 1–2, 4–5) reuses the owner's own 5-phase standardization prompt; the genuinely new piece is Phase 3, the human color gate (owner gives 4 brand colors + weights, AI derives the full semantic + light/dark palette and verifies WCAG 2.2 AA contrast, owner approves the whole set). It anchors every project to one central master standard, `60-Design/design-systems/design-system-standard.md` (owner-provided framework: token 3-tier ci/dna, W3C DTCG 2025.10, WCAG 2.2 AA, multi-tenant theming), and bakes in the INC-9085 in-place-vs-showcase ask plus backward-compatible MIGRATION rules so it never wrecks a live client site.

As of 2026-06-28, `Use BusinessPlan` v1.0 is added (22 → 23) as the first file of a new **Project OS** set — four standard per-project markdown files an AI reads/updates so it never loses the project's big picture: `BusinessPlan` (this one), plus the planned `OverviewProgress`, `FeatureSpec`, `DesignSystem`. Grounded in a prior-art scan (Cline Memory Bank, AGENTS.md, GitHub Spec Kit, Aider read-only conventions, W3C DTCG): the design borrows two-layer files (lean read-every-time `.project/BusinessPlan.md` + deep `.project/BusinessPlan-Full.md`), [fact]/[assumption] tagging to fight staleness, lean-file token discipline, and a check-then-create-or-update shortcut. It does NOT duplicate planning logic — it calls the existing `Use Business Plan` / `Use SaaS Opus Master Prompt` as the engine, and `Use SaaS Opus Master Prompt` is merged in (kept verbatim, not deleted) as its SaaS-mode engine. Close-chat tie-in: `Use Close Chat` is bumped to v2.1 with a capability-based Business Plan Sync step that updates the files only when the session actually changed something business-relevant, then emits a before→after report. Standard location is one folder per project (`.project/`) to avoid root clutter; portable across VPS + laptop by resolving the repo root from git instead of hardcoded paths.

As of 2026-07-04, `Use AI Relay` is upgraded to v2.2 (catalog to v0.2) adding brain tiers so the most expensive model is used only when it earns its cost: Fable 5 (`claude-fable-5`) joins as a special-brain callable only for tasks graded "hard" by a fixed rubric (catalog §6: ≥3 systems touched, security/permissions/money/PII, new architecture, hard-to-reverse, or 2 failed fix rounds) or via the escalation ladder (issue fails the gate twice → Fable rewrites only the thinking/brief, never code); Opus 4.8 stays the default brain with a 4.7→4.6 fallback chain. Coders are auto-picked from a new task-type routing table (catalog §7). relay-call spec gains a per-session Fable call cap, a cooldown for repeatedly failing tools, and a relay-report daily spend summary. Design grounded in a live GitHub survey (2026-07-04): `musistudio/claude-code-router` 35.5k stars, `BerriAI/litellm` 52.5k, `Aider-AI/aider` 47k, `BeehiveInnovations/pal-mcp-server` 11.6k, `lm-sys/RouteLLM` 5.1k. Two ideas are parked for a later phase: aider-style architect/editor two-step, and cross-vendor voting for high-risk merges. Later the same day, block B closed: `relay-call.py` + `gate-run.py` already existed in the Hermes Agent repo (`scripts/ai-relay/` — the vault doc was stale); they were upgraded in place (fable brain adapter + separate call cap, per-issue round cap across coders, cooldown for repeat-failing tools, a built-in YAML fallback reader fixing a real silently-ignored-config bug on machines without PyYAML) and a new `relay-report.py` daily usage summary was added; all smoke-tested 9/9 on the notebook including one real Fable call through `relay-call`. Status is now tooling-ready (notebook + VPS confirmed 2026-07-04 via one-time install-local.sh); Opus 4.7/4.6 model access remains the only unverified item.

As of 2026-07-04 (documentation-governance pass), a 25-shortcut review closed 8 documentation gaps (labels, cross-references, and light guardrail lines only — no shortcut's core behavior was rewritten; Review Chat and Use Summary each gained a small guardrail line inside their prompt blocks): Review Chat v2.2 now declares schema: memory-schema-v1.1 as a Close-Chat companion (not a version-lock lifecycle member) and its stray trailing code fence was removed; Use AI Pair v1.3 is marked superseded_by use-ai-relay while keeping status: active so alias lookups still resolve (kept as a no-relay fallback; its default team is stale vs catalog §7); the business trio gained explicit cross-links plus an engine-selection rule in Use BusinessPlan (SaaS → SaaS Opus engine, otherwise → Use Business Plan engine, never both in one job); routing tables were added to the design group (Impeccable / Create Design System / WOW Resource) and the content pair (Create Content → Blog Auto); AI Relay Catalog is promoted to active v0.3 (frontmatter + in-body "draft" wording reconciled) with a version pin to use-ai-relay ≥ v2.3, VPS-tool statuses kept marked unverified; the Use AI Relay registry row and its v2.2 status paragraph were reconciled to the real v2.3 tooling-ready state (block B closed, notebook + VPS confirmed); and Use Create Content's H1 was corrected from v1.0 to v1.3 to match its frontmatter.

